=Lu You 陸游 (1125-1210)=
==Literature==
===PhD Dissertations===
* Michael Sherman Duke: The life and work of Lu You (1125-1210), University of California, Berkeley, 1975
* Martin Gerald Backstrom: The castles of Shu: Dream motives in the poetry of Lu You (1125-1210), University of California, Berkeley, 1989
===Monographs===
* [[Ho Peng Yoke]], [[Goh Thean Chye]], and [[Beda Lim]]: Lu Yu, The Poet-Alchemist. Occasional Paper 13, Faculty of Asian Studies, Canberra: The Australian National University, 1972
* [[Burton Watson]]: The Old Man Who Does As He Pleases: Selections from the Poetry and Prose of Lu Yu. New York: Columbia University Press, 1973
* [[Michael Duke]]: Lu You. Twayne, 1977
* 張春樹, Joan Smythe: South China in the Twelfth Century: A Translation of Lu Yu's Travel Diaries, July 3 - December 6, 1170, Hong Kong: The Chinese University Press, 1981
* David M. Gordon: The Wild Old Man. Poems of Lu Yu. Berkeley, Ca: North Point Press, 1984